how ethernet works

Ethernet uses cables and routers, which have evolved over time to get faster, more
moduler, and more durable. It's used as a means to send data packets from one
node on a network to another to form the internet


how internet works

The internet works by sending data packets from various nodes on a network to each other allowing them all to exchange information with each other. A webstie for
example if just a file or a group of file on a server that are sent to any machine
that sends a request to view them

what is the arpanet

It is a precursor to the internet used mainly by universities. It would send data from one terminal to another. 

